com.ixortalk.udini.android.sdk

Class UdiniCallbackAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ixortalk.udini.android.sdk.UdiniCallbackAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    UdiniCallback

    public class UdiniCallbackAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
implements UdiniCallback
    Convenience class that provides an empty implementation for all interface methods. Can be used when a user is only interested in implementing a handful of features.

      • onUdiniDeviceInCooldown

        public void onUdiniDeviceInCooldown(UdiniDevice device,
                                    long remainingTimeMillis)
        Description copied from interface: UdiniCallback
        The Udini SDK reports a device entering a cooldown period whenever communication with that device has successfully ended. During cooldown the SDK will not attempt to automatically connect with the device. Once the cooldown is over the device will be treated as normal.
        Specified by:
        onUdiniDeviceInCooldown in interface UdiniCallback
        Parameters:
        device - the device that describes the BLE device in cooldown
        remainingTimeMillis - the time in milliseconds the device will stay in cooldown
        See Also:
        UdiniOptions.coolDownPeriodMillis()
